{
  "texts": [
    "Material sensingMetasurface technology plays a significant role in material sensing, particularly enabling high-precision spectral detection.",
    "This technology has been widely applied in the fields of biology and chemistry [214]- [217].",
    "In the field of biology, metasensors are commonly used to detect biomolecules, cells, microorganisms, and other biological entities.",
    "In the field of chemistry, metasensors are employed for analyzing chemical reactions and material properties.",
    "The precise spectral analysis provided by metasurface sensors holds great potential for important applications in medical diagnostics, environmental monitoring, and the study of new materials.In the field of biology, mid-infrared spectroscopy is often utilized for identifying various biomolecules such as proteins, lipids, nucleic acids, and polysaccharides."
  ]
}